{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place parsley in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","Place garlic in mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add onions, celery and oil then chop <b>4 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>4 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add wine and rice then, without measuring cup, cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Scrape base of mixing bowl with spatula to loosen rice.","Add tomatoes, vegetable stock, bay leaf, saffron, cayenne pepper (if using), salt and pepper then cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>.","Add mixed seafood, stir in gently with spatula then cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 0.5<b>.","Remove bay leaf. Add butter, juice from ½ lemon and ¾ reserved parsley then stir in gently with spatula. Taste risotto and adjust seasoning if desired, then leave to rest for 2 minutes with lid on. Meanwhile, cut remaining lemon half into 6 thin wedges. Serve immediately, garnished with lemon wedges and remaining chopped parsley."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["25 g fresh parsley","2 garlic cloves","150 g onions, quartered","80 g celery stalks, cut in pieces (2 cm)","25 g olive oil","200 g dry white wine","400 g risotto rice (e.g. Arborio, carnaroli)","250 g tinned chopped tomatoes","600 g vegetable stock, hot","1 dried bay leaf","1 pinch saffron","1 pinch ground cayenne pepper (optional)","½ tsp fine sea salt, or to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper, or to taste","500 g frozen mixed seafood, (e.g. prawns, clams, mussels, squid), defrosted","70 g unsalted butter, diced (1 cm)","1 lemon"]}],"id":"r76669","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-UzS7ebQlYZA\/XZQGqMTy2yI\/AAAAAAAAcAc\/zkw6e19RvP82iidVlba0xoMHKfN94-q_gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_VasYOVHAIDcrMti7.png","title":"Seafood Risotto","publishedAt":"2015-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"19.3 g","fat":"16.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"59.9 g","calories":"1918 kJ \/ 458 kcal"},"basicInfo":["medium","20m","40m","6 portions"]}